message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper involves the use of deep learning models for image analysis and classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the application of these models is in the medical field, specifically in the diagnosis of congenital heart disease, which could also fall under the medical informatics (cs.MED) sub-category. The use of deep learning models for medical image analysis also involves the use of neural networks, which could fall under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NEURON) sub-category.
